EAST LONDON -  The late Xhosa king Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu's memorial service will be conducted on Wednesday at the Abbotsford Christian Centre. The memorial is one of the countrywide services set to take place The funeral will be held at his birthplace, Nqadu Royal Place, near Willowvale in the Eastern Cape on Saturday. READ: AmaXhosa king dies aged 51 The family says memorial services are to be held in Cape Town, Johannesburg, Bloemfontein and Zimbabwe. The royal family has thanked the public for its support during their time of bereavement.